rawContent:
#ActuallyAutistic #Depression #Trauma TW

Things came up in me today.. And I need to let it out..
I find competitions so bad in principle. It was so difficult for me to keep up at school (after the traumatic break of my parents anyway, I was 6 y/o), even if the others didn't really notice, because I masked.
When I was really good at something, I never wanted to be better than the others. Because I didn't want the others to feel worse because of me. So I hid with my talents so many times.
I still feel the same today.
I've also been told so many times that I'm arrogant and selfish when I'm happy that I've done something very well and I'm confident.. that I'll probably never get rid of this break in me. Also people said to me, you get everything on the serving plate anyway, you have pretty privilege and are intentionally shit to me.
Then I just want to vanish into thin air and not be in this world anymore.
It feels like I have no rights to feel bad bc I have this face. It feels like I am not allowed to be confident bc it seems arrogant. It feels like I should shut my mouth forever and stop to "feel" bc my struggles and being autistic "isn't that bad". It feels like being on this earth harms others. But I want that ppl are lucky and feel well.
And I ask myself.. why tf am I here?!
